node.text:
In 1987, a 13-year-old Rasmus became enamored by Rap music.⁣
⁣
He began writing & rhyming for fun with friends while dreaming of one day recording. Today he is sharing his dream come true via this video made in a fun/humoristic spirit with dear friends.⁣
⁣
Featuring @sorenledet on guitar & the legendary @djnoizecph on scratch.⁣

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Restaurant Geranium on September 12, 2021. May be an image of 11 people, people standing and indoor.

node.text:
Remembering Great Moments ~

In 2019 we cooked alongside friends @bjornfrantzen, @danielberlinkrogiskanetranas, @marcus.jernmark & @tristinfarmer  @zen.singapore . On Septmber 1st, 2021 we congratulated them as Zén was awarded 3 stars in the Michelin Guide Singapore! Uniting across borders to share our passion is a unique & rewarding experience which we look forward to doing again & again.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Restaurant Geranium on September 08, 2021 tagging @sorenledet. May be an image of 11 people, people standing, suit and outdoors.

node.text: These are a few of the smiling faces from our front of house team who look forward to welcoming you to Geranium. We are all so very happy to be back in service and doing what we love. Hope to see you soon!

node.text:
Remembering Great Moments ~

Over the summer Rasmus was awarded "Årets Plantevenlige Kok" or plant friendly chef of the year for his creation of & work with Angelika, our 100% plant-based restaurant. The annual awards are hosted by @plantevaekst , a local ogranization that works to promote plant-based opportunities in Denmark.  Eating more vegetables is a great way to support good health & the environment. Angelika is on hold for the moment but we hope it will return in the future.

July 2021

📸 madfeed.co

node.text: Clean, fresh water is one of mother nature's greatest gifts to mankind. Honoring & protecting the environment is important to us and something we strive to do better each day. One of the ways we do that is to offer our guests filtered water instead of bottled water. In 2007, we were one of the first restaurants in Denmark to install a filtration system which runs the already great water here in Copenhagen through a series of filters to ensure the utmost purity and taste.

Remembering Great Moments ~

Have you ever wondered what the Geranium team has for dinner on work days?

Our weekly staff meals consist of: vegan, vegetarian, fish & meat for each of our opening days. Here's a look at one of our vegan days. Healthy, delicious, colorful & nutritious, the cornestones of our meal plan.
